# arch-research-doc-lora-review-pattern — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-04-13)

**Changed by:** Session — Myrmidon swarm review of idea 4.5 (Learned Residual Flow Control)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added "Layer Pruning / Residual Gating Pattern" section to the review checklist
- Added 5 new Failed Attempts entries for layer-pruning-specific review errors
- Added layer-pruning-specific literature gap checklist items
- Updated When to Use to include layer pruning / residual gating ideas
- Updated tags to include `layer-pruning`, `residual-gating`, `static-inference`
- Updated description to cover the new idea type

### Why
The 4.5 (Learned Residual Flow Control) review session revealed that the existing skill covered
LoRA/low-rank ideas only. Layer pruning ideas have a distinct set of red flags:
- "Static at inference" claims that don't distinguish frozen soft gates (no speedup) from model surgery (real speedup)
- Training overhead misattributed from Hyper-Connections SHC to scalar gates
- Missing Mixture of Depths citation (most common gap)
- "Frankle and Carlin" misspelling vs correct "Frankle and Carbin"
- 4.4+4.5 composition that is order-dependent (not commutative)

